_⚠️ Potential issue_ | _🟠 Major_ | _⚡ Quick win_

**Move source enumeration off the main actor.**

Line 580 and Line 628 synchronously call `capture.availableSources()` on `@MainActor`, despite Line 255 noting HAL enumeration can stall UI. This can freeze menubar interactions during restore/refresh ticks.  


<details>
<summary>Suggested fix</summary>

```diff
+    private func fetchAvailableSourcesOffMain() async throws -> [CaptureSource] {
+        try await Task.detached(priority: .userInitiated) { [capture] in
+            try capture.availableSources()
+        }.value
+    }
+
     private func restoreSourceFromDefaults() {
         guard let bundleID = defaults.string(forKey: AppViewModelDefaultsKey.sourceBundleID),
               !bundleID.isEmpty
         else { return }
-        do {
-            let candidates = try capture.availableSources()
-            if let match = candidates.first(where: { $0.bundleIdentifier == bundleID }) {
-                currentSource = match
+        Task { `@MainActor` [weak self] in
+            guard let self else { return }
+            do {
+                let candidates = try await fetchAvailableSourcesOffMain()
+                if let match = candidates.first(where: { $0.bundleIdentifier == bundleID }) {
+                    currentSource = match
+                }
+            } catch {
+                logger.warning("Source restore failed: \(error.localizedDescription, privacy: .public)")
             }
-        } catch {
-            logger.warning("Source restore failed: \(error.localizedDescription, privacy: .public)")
         }
     }
@@
     public func refreshAvailableSources() {
-        do {
-            availableSources = try capture.availableSources()
-        } catch {
-            logger.warning("Source refresh failed: \(error.localizedDescription, privacy: .public)")
-        }
+        Task { `@MainActor` [weak self] in
+            guard let self else { return }
+            do {
+                availableSources = try await fetchAvailableSourcesOffMain()
+            } catch {
+                logger.warning("Source refresh failed: \(error.localizedDescription, privacy: .public)")
+            }
+        }
     }
```
</details>


Also applies to: 626-631

<details>
<summary>🤖 Prompt for AI Agents</summary>

```
Verify each finding against current code. Fix only still-valid issues, skip the
rest with a brief reason, keep changes minimal, and validate.

In `@Sources/ViewModel/AppViewModel.swift` around lines 575 - 586,
restoreSourceFromDefaults calls capture.availableSources() on the main actor
which can stall the UI; move the HAL/source enumeration off the MainActor, e.g.
perform capture.availableSources() inside a detached/background Task and await
its result, then hop back to the MainActor only to update UI-bound state
(currentSource) and to log; apply the same pattern to the other call site around
the block noted (the other availableSources() usage in this file).
```

</details>

